| HistoryText             =  A group of androids built by a black-ops project who went somewhat rogue based on programming by their creator [[David Jenkins (Earth-616)|David Jenkins]] which led them to hunt down and destroy other renegade, dangerous and morally repugnant black-ops projects.{{r|Livewires Vol 1 6}}

| Equipment               = Disguises
| Transportation          = Van
| Weapons                 = Firearms, various pieces of technology salvaged from black-ops projects they've destroyed

| Notes                   = 
* The Livewire's technology is largely descended from that of the [[Mannites]] and [[Strategic Hazard Intervention Espionage_Logistics Directorate (Earth-616)|S.H.I.E.L.D.]] [[Life-Model Decoy]]s, though modified with additional technology they've picked up on past missions.
| Trivia                  = 
* Cornfed told Stem Cell that his team doesn't like being called "robots", believing it to be a pejorative slur and referring to it as the "r-word". The word comes from a Czech word, robota, meaning "forced labor". Instead, they suggested "semi-autonomous, artificially intelligent, limited-nanofunction, humanform mecha constructs," as well as also often referring to one another and other such beings as "mecha".{{r|Livewires Vol 1 1|2}}{{r|Black Panther and the Agents of Wakanda Vol 1 5}}
